Yeah I think the idea of agents being automated to do tasks isn't groundbreaking because of the fact we already have task automation through simple things like python or even apps like zapier

But the innovation will be with the scale that they can be done as well as the agents talking to each other
10:30
An example from OpenAI is that while you can have your own personal agent make restaurant reservations or even write reviews after, that's cool but not groundbreaking.

THe next level is the agent calling up 300 different restaurants to find the best reservation for you, including the type of booth or window view you like for a table

The next level after that is that not only is the agent calling 300 places, but the 300 places also have an agent themselves handling the inbound

So the efficiency becomes more fluid and scalable
